  "business_context": "Phone-call records capture voice-touchpoint metadata that generic Activity records can't structure: duration matters for sales-rep productivity reporting; direction (inbound vs outbound) drives different workflows (inbound calls usually trigger SLA-tracked responses); call recordings (with consent) feed quality-assurance reviews and AI coaching tools. Modeling diverges: Salesforce historically used Task with TaskSubtype=Call; Salesforce Voice and Service Cloud Voice introduce a dedicated VoiceCall object. HubSpot has Call as an Engagement type with HubSpot Calling integration. EspoCRM has Call as a separate first-class entity. CiviCRM uses Activity records with activity_type=Phone Call. Attio has Calls as a separate object (with call recording integrations). Bloomerang uses Interaction subtype=Phone Call. NPSP follows Salesforce. When interviewing clients, surface \"Phone Call\" by asking whether they need to track call duration, distinguish inbound from outbound, or capture call recordings — if any of those, a structured phone-call entity is preferred over generic Activity logging.",
  "catalog_id": "activity-phone-call",
  "common_synonyms": [
    "Call",
    "Voice Call",
    "Logged Call",
    "Phone Conversation"
  ],
  "data_model_role": "log",
